snippet.textDisplay: I love you no matter what you have been through. I heard about your transition before I watched this video and it changes nothing about how I feel about you. I love you to death, I always have and I always will. I think you’re so brave for telling people your past. I hope you read this and believe that the people who are a part of your community who love you most will always love you no matter what, no matter who you are. Me personally, I believe you are truly Nikkie and that is who you will always be in my heart. I don’t know what you are going through or what you have been through but my parents are extremely religious. Jehovah’s wittinesses. I left the religion at about 13 or 14 years old. My cousins soon followed. I came out as bisexual which is a big deal for them and both my cousins are lesbian so I never had the support I wanted but with my friends and the people around me that I loved it helped me a lot to know that it was ok to be who I am. I’m sorry I know this is a long message but I never know if people read what I say. I know I am not transgendered and I only know one person who is at the very beginning of their transition that I don’t really talk to because they’re dating my very best friend but I really appreciate everything you’ve said and I will support you always. I know everything isn’t always easy and when I watch my favourite youtubers
